HEADWORD: Magnase black
<hw>Mag"nase black`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Paint.)</fld> <def>A black
pigment which dries rapidly when mixed with oil, and is of intense
body.</def> <rj><au>Fairholt.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

